land|Mackay]].\n\n===Squad===\n{{Gold Coast AFL Women's current squad}}\n\n===Season summaries===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%\"\n! colspan=\"9\" | Gold Coast AFLW honour roll\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%;\"\n! Season !! Final position\n!Coach\n!Captain(s)!! Best and fairest !! Leading goal kicker\n|-style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n|[[2020 AFL Women's season|2020]]\n|TBC\n|[[David Lake (coach)|David Lake]]\n|[[Leah Kaslar]] & [[Sam Virgo]]\n|TBC\n|TBC\n|}\n\n==NEAFL team==\n{{Main|Australian Football League reserves affiliations}}\nThe Gold Coast Suns have fielded a [[Reserve team|reserves team]] beneath the AFL team in the [[North East Australian Football League]] (NEAFL) competition since 2011. The reserves team has been reasonably competitive, qualifying for finals on two out of four occasions, notwithstanding a disastrous 2014 campaign which saw the team fail to win a match all season.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;\"\n! Season !! Win-Loss !! Ladder position !! Finals result !! Best & Fairest\n|-\n| [[2011 NEAFL season|2011]] || 11-7 || 3rd || Semi-final || [[Jacob Gillbee]]\n|-\n| [[2012 NEAFL season|2012]] || 9-9 || 5th || Elimination final || [[Alik Magin]]\n|-\n| [[2013 NEAFL season|2013]] || 10-7 || 6th || DNQ || [[Jack Martin (Australian footballer)|Jack Martin]]\n|-\n| [[2014 NEAFL season|2014]] || 0-18 || 14th || DNQ || [[Leigh Osborne]]\n|-\n| [[2015 NEAFL season|2015]] || 8-10 || 7th || DNQ || [[Tyrone Downie (footballer)|Tyrone Downie]]\n|-\n| [[2016 NEAFL season|2016]] || 8-10 || 6th || Elimination Final || [[Keegan Brooksby]]\n|-\n| [[2017 NEAFL season|2017]] || 10-8 || 4th || Preliminary Final || [[Darcy Macpherson]]\n|-\n| [[2018 NEAFL season|2018]] || 7-11 || 8th || DNQ || [[Jacob Dawson]]\n|-\n| [[2019 NEAFL season|2019]] || 8-10 || 7th || DNQ || [[Tom Nicholls]]\n|}\n\n==Honour board ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 85%\"\n! colspan=\"11\" |<big>Gold Coast Suns Honour Board</big> \n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 85%\"\n! colspan=\"11\" | TAC Cup\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 85%\"\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Year'''\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Position'''\n!\n{{Tooltip|'''W-L-D'''|Win-loss-draw (Includes finals/league results only)}}\n!{{Tooltip|'''%'''|Percentage PF/PA (Includes finals/league results only)}}\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Chairman'''\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''CEO'''\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Coach'''\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Captain'''\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Club'''<br />'''Champion'''\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\" |'''Leading'''<br />'''Goalkicker'''\n|- style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|[[2009 TAC Cup season|2009]]||5\n|10-7-1\n|111\n||John Witheriff\n|| Travis Auld ||[[Guy McKenna]]||[[Marc Lock]]||[[Marc Lock]]\n||Matt Fowler\n|43\n|-\n! colspan=\"11\" |<small>Victorian Football League</small>\n|- style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|[[2010 VFL season|2010]]||10\n|5-12-1\n|83\n||John Witheriff\n|| Travis Auld\n||[[Guy McKenna]]||[[Marc Lock]]||[[Sam Iles]]||[[Charlie Dixon (Australian footballer)|Charlie Dixon]]<br />[[Brandon Matera]] \n|22\n|-\n! colspan=\"11\" |<small>Australian Football League</small>\n|- style=\"font-size: 85%;\"\n|[[2011 AFL season|2011]]||17\n|3-19-0\n|56||John Witheriff\n|| Travis Auld\n||[[Guy McKenna]]||[[Gary Ablett Jr.]]||[[Gary Ablett Jr.]]\n|[[Danny Stanley]]\n|20\n|-\n|<small>[[2012 AFL season|2012]]</small>\n|<small>17</small>\n|<small>3-19-0</small>\n|<small>61</small>\n|<small>John Witheriff</small>\n|<small>Travis Auld</small>\n|<small>[[Guy McKenna]]</small>\n|<small>[[Gary Ablett Jr.]]</small>\n|<small>[[Gary Ablett Jr.]]</small>\n|<small>[[Gary Ablett Jr.]]</small>\n|<small>26</small>\n|-\n