 September 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706104510/http://goldcoastfc.com.au/news-and-media/news/west-australian-swallow-joins-gold-coast-football-club/page-2/|archivedate=6 July 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"2010 draft\">{{cite web|title=Gold Coast SUNS outstanding results at the 2010 NAB Draft |date=18 November 2010 |url=http://www.goldcoastfc.com.au/news-and-media/news/gold-coast-suns-outstanding-results-at-the-2010-nab-draft/ |publisher=Gold Coast FC |accessdate=18 November 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101129091217/http://goldcoastfc.com.au/news-and-media/news/gold-coast-suns-outstanding-results-at-the-2010-nab-draft/ |archivedate=29 November 2010 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n| Western Australia\n| [[East Fremantle Football club|East Fremantle Sharks]]\n| National Draft (1)\n|-\n| [[Harley Bennell]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| Western Australia\n| [[Peel Thunder]]\n| National Draft (2)\n|-\n| [[Sam Day (Australian rules footballer)|Sam Day]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| South Australia\n| [[Sturt Football Club|Sturt Double Blues]]\n| National Draft (3)\n|-\n| [[Josh Caddy]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| Victoria\n| [[Northern Knights]]\n| National Draft (7)\n|-\n| [[Dion Prestia]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| Victoria\n| [[Calder Cannons]]\n| National Draft (9)\n|-\n| [[Daniel Gorringe]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| South Australia\n| [[Norwood Football Club|Norwood Redlegs]]\n| National Draft (10)\n|-\n| [[Tom Lynch (Australian footballer, born 1992)|Tom Lynch]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| Victoria\n| [[Dandenong Stingrays]]\n| National Draft (11)\n|-\n| [[Seb Tape]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| South Australia\n| [[Glenelg Football Club|Glenelg Tigers]]\n| National Draft (13)\n|-\n| [[Jeremy Taylor (Australian footballer)|Jeremy Taylor]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| Victoria\n| [[Geelong Falcons]]\n| National Draft (39)\n|-\n| [[Jacob Gillbee]]<ref name=\"2010 draft\"/>\n| Tasmania\n| [[Lauderdale Football Club|Lauderdale Bombers]]\n| National Draft (49)\n|-\n| [[Nathan Ablett]]\n| | Victoria\n| [[Geelong Football Club]]\n| Pre Season Draft (1)\n|}\n\n==Current squad==\n{{Gold Coast Suns current squad}}\n\n==Coaching staff==\n* '''Senior coach:''' \n:* [[Stuart Dew]]\n\n* '''Assistant coaches:'''\n:* [[Matthew Primus]]\n:* [[Andy Lovell]]\n:* [[Ashley Prescott]]\n:* [[Dean Solomon]]\n* '''Development coach:'''\n:* [[Matthew Lappin]]\n\n* '''Coaching advisor:'''\n:* [[Malcolm Blight]]\n\n* '''[[North East Australian Football League|NEAFL]] coach'''\n:* Stephen Daniel\n<small>''Click [https://web.archive.org/web/20150910131254/http://www.goldcoastfc.com.au/team/football-staff/coaching-staff here] for more information on Gold Coast's coaching staff''</small>\n\n==AFL Women's team==\nIn September 2017, Gold Coast were granted a license by the AFL to compete in the [[AFL Women's]] league from the start of the [[2020 AFL Women's season|2020 season]].<ref name=\"ExpansionABCNews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-09-27/tasmania-nth-melb-geelong-win-new-aflw-licences-for-2019/8992508|title=AFLW: Tasmania-North Melbourne and Geelong win licenses to field teams in 2019|publisher=ABC News|date=27 September 2017}}</ref> The club shares home games between [[Carrara Stadium]], [[Fankhauser Reserve]] in nearby [[Southport, Queensland|Southport]], and the [[Ray Mitchell Oval|Great Barrier Reef Arena]] in [[Mackay, Queensland|Mackay]].\n\n===Squad===\n{{Gold Coast AFL Women's current squad}}\n\n===Season summaries===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%\"\n! colspan=\"9\" | Gold Coast AFLW honour roll\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 87%;\"\n! Season !! Final position\n!Coach\n!Captain(s)!! Best and fairest !! Leading goal kicker\n|-style=\"font-size: 87%;\"\n|[[2020 AFL Women's season|2020]]\n|TBC\n|[[David Lake (coach)|David Lake]]\n|[[Leah Kaslar]] & [[Sam Virgo]]\n|TBC\n|TBC\n|}\n\n==NEAFL team==\n{{Main|Australian Football League reserves affiliations}}\nThe Gold Coast Suns have fielded a [[Reserve team|reserves team]] beneath the AFL team in the [[North East Australian Football League]] (NEAFL) competition since 2011. The reserves team has been reasonably competitive, qualifying for finals on two out of four occasions, notwithstanding a disastrous 2014 campaign which saw the team fail to win a match all season.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;\"\n! Season !! Win-Loss !! Ladder position !! Finals result !! Best & Fairest\n|-\n| [[2011 NEAFL season|2011]] || 11-7 || 3rd || Semi-final || [[Jacob Gillbee]]\n|-\n| [[2012 NEAFL season|2012]] || 9-9 || 5th || Elimination final || [[Alik Magin]]\n|-\n| [[2013 NEAFL season|2013]] || 10-7 || 6th || DNQ || [[Jack Martin (Australian footballer)|Jack Martin]]\n|-\n| [[2014 NEAFL season|2014]] || 0-18 || 14th || DNQ || [[Leigh Osborne]]\n|-\n| [[2015 NEAFL season|2015]] || 8-10 || 7th || DNQ || [[Tyrone Downie (footballer)|Tyrone Downie]]\n|-\n| [[2016 NEAFL season|2016]] || 8-10 || 6th || Elimination Final || [[Keegan Brooksby]]\n|-\n| [[2017 NEAFL season|2017]] || 10-8 || 4th || Preliminary Final || [[Darcy Macpherson]]\n|-\n| [[2018 NEAFL season|2018]] || 7-11 || 8th || DNQ || [[Jacob Dawson]]\n|-\n| [[2019 NEAFL season|2019]] || 8-10 || 7th || DNQ || [[Tom Nicholls]]\n|}\n\n==Honour board ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 85%\"\n! colspan=\"11\" |<big>Gold Coast Suns Honour Board</big> \n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 85%\"\n! colspan=\"11\" | TAC Cup\n|- style=\"background:#bdb76b;font-size: 85%\"\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Year'''\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Position'''\n!\n{{Tooltip|'''W-L-D'''|Win-loss-draw (Includes finals/league results only)}}\n!{{Tooltip|'''%'''|Percentage PF/PA (Includes finals/league results only)}}\n!  style=\"text-align:center; background:#f0f0f0;\"|'''Chairman'''\n!  style=\"text-a