0||6||0\n|-\n|22||{{flagicon|POR}}||FW||[[N\u00e9lson Oliveira]]||2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|24||{{flagicon|ENG}}||DF||[[Tyler Blackett]]||4||1||0||0||0||0||4||1\n|-\n|26||{{flagicon|ARG}}||GK||[[Emiliano Mart\u00ednez]]||2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|27||{{flagicon|ENG}}||DF||[[Omar Richards]]||1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|32||{{flagicon|IRN}}||MF||[[Saeid Ezatolahi]]||1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|35||{{flagicon|ENG}}||MF||[[Andy Rinomhota]]||5||0||0||0||1||0||6||0\n|-\n|38||{{flagicon|IRL}}||MF||[[Liam Kelly (footballer, born 1995)|Liam Kelly]]||2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|43||{{flagicon|ENG}}||FW||[[Danny Loader]]||1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|colspan=\"13\"|''Players away on loan:''\n|-\n|8 ||{{flagicon|IRL}}||MF||[[David Meyler]]||1||0||0||0||0||0||1||0\n|-\n|colspan=\"13\"|''Players who left Reading during the season:''\n|-\n|7 ||{{flagicon|CUR}}||MF||[[Leandro Bacuna]]||4||1||0||0||0||0||4||1\n|-\n|19||{{flagicon|ENG}}||MF||[[Josh Sims (footballer)|Josh Sims]]||4||0||0||0||0||0||4||0\n|-\n|20||{{flagicon|POR}}||DF||[[Tiago Ilori]]||2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n! colspan=4 | Total\n!80||3||1||0||2||0||83||3\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n{{Cnote2 Begin}}\n{{Cnote2 End}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n=== Match reports ===\n{{reflist|35em|group=Report}}\n\n{{Reading F.C. seasons}}\n{{2018\u201319 in English football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2018-19 Reading F.C. season}}\n[[Category:2018\u201319 EFL Championship by team|Reading]]\n[[Category:Reading F.C. seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club season\n| club               = [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]\n| season             = 2018\u201319\n| manager            = [[Paul Clement (football manager)|Paul Clement]] <br> <small>(until 6 December)</small> <br> [[Scott Marshall (footballer)|Scott Marshall]] <small>(Caretaker)</small><br><small>(6\u201322 December)</small> <br> [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Gomes|Jos\u00e9 Gomes]] <br><small> (from 22 December 2018)</small>\n| stadium            = [[Madejski Stadium]]\n| league             = [[Football League Championship|Championship]]\n| league result      = 20th\n| cup1               = [[FA Cup]]\n| cup1 result        = Third round <br> (vs. [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]])\n| cup2               = [[EFL Cup]]\n| cup2 result        = Second round <br> (vs. [[Watford F.C.|Watford]])\n| league topscorer   = [[Yakou M\u00e9\u00eft\u00e9]] (12)\n| season topscorer   = Yakou M\u00e9\u00eft\u00e9 (13)\n| highest attendance = 17,255 vs [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] <br><small>(22 April 2019)</small>\n| lowest attendance  = 11,271 vs [[Blackburn Rovers F.C.|Blackburn Rovers]] <br><small>(13 February 2019)</small>\n| average attendance = {{formatnum:{{#expr: (((16923+13318+14352+12822+12409+13568+14532+14455+14952+14414+12066+14943+15644+15034+17458+11271+15958+15401+17101+16771+16892+17255+17247)/23) round 0)}}}} {{small|(5 May 2019)}}\n| pattern_la1   = _reading1819h\n| pattern_b1    = _reading1819h\n| pattern_ra1   = _reading1819h\n| pattern_sh1   = _whitesides\n| pattern_so1   = _whitetop\n| leftarm1      = FFFFFF\n| body1         = FFFFFF\n| rightarm1     = FFFFFF\n| shorts1       = 0000FF\n| socks1        = 0000FF\n| pattern_la2   = _reading1819a\n| pattern_b2    = _reading1819a\n| pattern_ra2   = _reading1819a\n| pattern_sh2   = _whitesides\n| pattern_so2   = _reading1819a\n| leftarm2      = 000000\n| body2         = 000000\n| rightarm2     = 000000\n| shorts2       = 000000\n| socks2        = 000000\n| prevseason         = [[2017\u201318 Reading F.C. season|2017\u201318]]\n| nextseason         = [[2019\u201320 Reading F.C. season|2019\u201320]]\n}}\nThe '''2018\u201319 season''' is [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]'s 148th year in existence and sixth consecutive season in the [[Football League Championship|Championship]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=History |url=http://www.statto.com/football/teams/reading/history |publisher=Statto}}</ref> and covers the period from 1 July 2018 to 30 June 2019.\n\n==Season review==\n===Pre-season===\nOn 18 May 2018, Reading announced that they would be taking part in a six-day pre-season training camp in [[Bad Erlach]], [[Austria]], with two friendlies scheduled to be played against as yet un-confirmed opposition.<ref>{{cite web|title=Destination Austria for the Royals|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/may/destination-austria--for-the-royals/|website=readingfc.co.uk|publisher=Reading F.C.|accessdate=18 May 2018|date=18 May 2018}}</ref> The [[EFL Cup]] first round draw took place on 15 June 2018, in [[Vietnam]], drawing Reading at home against [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Royals to host Birmingham City in Carabao Cup! |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/june/royals-to-host-birmingham-city-in-carabao-cup/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=15 June 2018 |date=15 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Lampard's Derby at Oldham in Carabao Cup |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44468336 |accessdate=15 June 2018 |publisher=[[BBC]] |date=15 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Transfers and contracts====\nReading announced their first summer signing on 17 May 2018, [[Andy Yiadom]] signed a four-year contract with Reading, officially joining his new club on 1 July after the expiration of his [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] contract.<ref name=\"Yiadom Signs\">{{cite web|title=Andy Yiadom to become Royals\u2019 first summer signing!|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/may/andy-yiadom-to-become-royals-first-summer-signing/|website=readingfc.co.uk|publisher=Reading F.C.|accessdate=17 May 2018|date=17 May 2018}}</ref> Reading's second summer signing was announced on 5 June, with [[David Meyler]] signing a two-year contract, with the option of an additional year, on a free transfer from [[Hull City A.F.C.|Hull City]] upon the conclusion of contract with them on 30 June.<ref name=\"David Meyler to sign for the Royals\"/> The following day, Reading announced that [[John O'Shea]] had signed a one-year contract to commence on 1 July 2018.<ref name=\"O'Shea Signs\">{{cite web|title=John O\u2019Shea is a Royal!|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/june/john-oshea-is-a-royal/|website=readingfc.co.uk|publisher=Reading F.C.|accessdate=6 June 2018|date=6 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 June, Reading announced that [[Andrija Novakovich]] had signed a new two-year contract with the club, and that he would spend the next season on loan at [[Eredivisie]] club [[Fortuna Sittard]].<ref name=\"Novakovich\">{{cite web |title=Novakovich agrees new Royals deal and seals Fortuna loan switch |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/june/novakovich-agrees-new-royals-deal-and-seals-fortuna-loan-switch/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=20 June 2018 |date=20 June 2018}}</ref> Two days after, it was announced that goalkeeper [[Lewis Ward (footballer)|Lewis Ward]] had also extended his contract with the club until the summer of 2020.<ref name=\"Goalkeeper Ward extends Royals deal\">{{cite web |title=Goalkeeper Ward extends Royals deal |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/june/goalkeeper-ward-extends-royals-deal/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=22 June 2018 |date=22 June 2018}}</ref> On 2 July, Reading announced that youngsters Jamal Balogun, Andre Burley, Cameron Green, Adam Liddle, Akinwale Odimayo, Moroyin Omolabi and Jazz Wallace had all signed their first professional contracts with the club, whilst goalkeeper [[Luke Southwood]] had also signed a new two-year contract.<ref name=\"Seven players sign first pro deals with Reading\">{{cite web |title=Seven players sign first pro deals with Reading |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/seven-players-sign-first-pro-deals-with-reading/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=2 July 2018 |date=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nReading signed [[Marc McNulty]] from [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]], on 6 July, to a four-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref name=\"Marc McNulty\">{{cite web |title=Signed! Marc McNulty is a Royal! |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/signed-marc-mcnulty-is-a-royal/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=8 July 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref> Two days later, it was announced that [[Danzell Gravenberch]] had re-joined [[K.S.V. Roeselare|KSV Roeselare]] on loan for second successive season.<ref name=\"Gravenberch\">{{cite news |title=Gravenberch rejoins Roeselare on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/gravenberch-rejoins-roeselare-on-loan |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=9 July 2018 |date=9 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 July, Reading parted company with striker [[Yann Kermorgant]] by mutual agreement<ref name=\"Kermorgant Leaves\">{{cite web |title=Royals and Kermorgant mutually part company |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/royals-and-kermorgant-mutually-part-company |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=10 July 2018 |date=10 July 2018}}</ref> and [[Tennai Watson]] joined [[AFC Wimbledon]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref name=\"Watson Loan\">{{cite web |title=Watson set for loan season as a Don |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/watson-set-for-loan-season-as-a-don |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=10 July 2018 |date=10 July 2018}}</ref> Reading announced that they had signed [[Darren Sidoel]] from [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] on a three-year contract on 17 July.<ref name=\"Sidoel\">{{cite news |title=Young Ajax prospect Darren Sidoel joins Royals\u2019 ranks |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/young-ajax-prospect-darren-sidoel-joins-royals-ranks |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=17 July 2018 |date=17 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nAcademy graduate J\u00f6kull Andr\u00e9sson agreed a two-year contract with Reading on 24 July, before joining [[Hungerford Town F.C.|Hungerford Town]] on loan until 1 January 2019.<ref name=\"J\u00f6kull Andr\u00e9sson\">{{cite web |title=Academy graduate J\u00f6kull Andr\u00e9sson agrees to two-year pro deal |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/academy-graduate-jokull-andresson-agrees-to-two-year-pro-deal |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=24 July 2018 |date=24 July 2018}}</ref> The following day, [[Joey van den Berg]] moved to [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC]] on a season-long loan deal,<ref name=\"van den Berg Loan\">{{cite web |title=Joey van den Berg heads to Holland on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/joey-van-den-berg-heads-to-holland-on-loan |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=25 July 2018 |date=25 July 2018}}</ref> whilst [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]] goalkeeper [[Sam Walker (footballer)|Sam Walker]] joined the club on a three-year deal.<ref name=\"Sam Walker\">{{cite web |title=Sam Walker signs for the Royals |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/sam-walker-signs-for-the-royals |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=25 July 2018 |date=25 July 2018}}</ref> On 27 July, [[Lewis Ward (footballer)|Lewis Ward]] joined [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] on a season-long loan.<ref name=\"Lewis Ward Northampton Town\">{{cite web |title=Lewis Ward links up with Northampton Town on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/lewis-ward-links-up-with-northampton-town-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=28 July 2018 |date=27 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Sam Baldock]] signed a three-year contract with Reading, joining from [[Brighton and Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton and Hove Albion]] on 30 July.<ref name=\"Sam Baldock\">{{cite web |title=Sam Baldock is a Royal!|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/sam-baldock-is-a-royal/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=30 July 2018 |date=30 July 2018}}</ref> The following day, Reading confirmed that [[George Evans (footballer, born 1994)|George Evans]] had moved to [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] for an undisclosed fee<ref name=\"George Evans Derby\">{{cite web |title=George Evans signs for Derby County |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/george-evans-signs-for-derby-county/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 July 2018 |date=31 July 2018}}</ref> and [[Sam Smith (footballer, born 1998)|Sam Smith]] joined [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] on a season-long loan.<ref name=\"Sam Smith Oxford\">{{cite web |title=Sam Smith seals loan switch to Oxford United |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/sam-smith-seals-loan-switch-to-oxford-united/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 July 2018 |date=31 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n====Matches====\nOn 30 June, Reading played their first pre-season fixture away at [[Eastleigh F.C.|Eastleigh]]. The Royals lost the fixture 2\u20131, with the [[National League (division)|National League]] side scoring a late winner through [[Ben Williamson (footballer)|Ben Williamson]]. Prior to this, [[Paul McCallum (footballer)|Paul McCallum]] had put the hosts ahead in the first half, before [[Leandro Bacuna]]'s equaliser. Reading played two different teams composed of first team players in either half.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/june/match-report-eastleigh-vs-reading/|title=Eastleigh 2-1 Royals|work=[[Reading F.C.]]|date=30 June 2018|accessdate=28 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 July, Reading faced [[EFL League One|League One]] outfit [[AFC Wimbledon]] at [[Kingsmeadow]]. Former-Royals loanee [[Kwesi Appiah]] put the hosts ahead, before [[Joe Pigott]] doubled their advantage just before the  break. [[Adrian Popa (footballer, born 1988)|Adrian Popa]] and [[Sam Smith (footballer, born 1998)|Sam Smith]] levelled the game with two goals in five minutes following the restart. [[Egli Kaja]] restored Wimbledon's lead, with Kane Crichlow wrapping up a 4\u20132 victory for the Dons with six minutes to play. As with the Eastleigh fixture, Reading fielded separate teams in either half.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/report--afc-wimbledon-vs-reading/|title=AFC Wimbledon 4-2 Royals|work=[[Reading F.C.]]|date=7 July 2018|accessdate=28 July 2018}}</ref> A 0\u20130 draw with [[Premier League]] [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] followed a week later at the [[Recreation Ground (Aldershot)|Recreation Ground]] in [[Aldershot]]. Twenty-one different players featured for Reading.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/pre-season--fulham-vs-reading/|title=Fulham 0-0 Reading|work=[[Reading F.C.]]|date=14 July 2018|accessdate=28 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nAs part of the club's training camp in [[Bad Erlach]], [[Austria]], the Royals faced Turkish giants [[Be\u015fikta\u015f J.K.|Be\u015fikta\u015f]] in [[Graz]], as part of the Turks' preparation for their [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] campaign. [[Ryan Babel]] and [[O\u011fuzhan \u00d6zyakup]] put Be\u015fikta\u015f into a two-goal lead in the second half, before Sam Smith and [[Mark McNulty]] levelled the contest in the final ten minutes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/pre-season--beikta-vs-reading/|title=Be\u015fikta\u015f 2-2 Reading|work=[[Reading F.C.]]|date=17 July 2018|accessdate=28 July 2018}}</ref> On the 20 July, Reading faced former Russian champions [[FC Rubin Kazan|Rubin Kazan]] in [[Ilz, Styria|Ilz]] with the sides playing out a 0\u20130 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/pre-season--reading-vs-rubin-kazan/|title=Reading 0-0 Rubin Kazan|work=[[Reading F.C.]]|date=20 July 2018|accessdate=28 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 July, Reading played their only home match of pre-season with the visit of [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]]. The Premier League side won 4\u20130, with goals from [[Alexander S\u00f8rloth]], [[Wilfried Zaha]] (two) and [[James Tomkins (footballer)|James Tomkins]], rounding of a winless pre-season for Reading.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/july/pre-season--reading-vs-crystal-palace/|title=Premier League Palace too good|work=[[Reading F.C.]]|date=28 July 2018|accessdate=28 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n===August===\nReading opened the season with a 2\u20131 home defeat against [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] on 3 August. Reading opened the scoring in the 52nd minute through [[J\u00f3n Da\u00f0i B\u00f6\u00f0varsson]], before [[Mason Mount]] equalised in the 60th minute and [[Tom Lawrence]] scored a last minute header to seal the victory for Derby County.<ref name=\"MATCHREPORT Derby County H (EFL)\" group=\"Report\">{{cite web|title=Reading 1\u20132 Derby County|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/matches/fixtures/first-team/201819/august/reading-vs-derby-county-on-03-aug-18/#|website=readingfc.co.uk|publisher=Reading F.C.|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> Reading's second game of the season saw them travel to [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on 11 August. A single [[Hillal Soudani]] goal in the 68th minute saw the host emerge victorious, and Reading dropping to the foot of the table.<ref name=\"MATCHREPORT Nottingham Forest A (EFL)\" group=\"Report\">{{cite web|title=Nottingham Forest 1\u20130 Reading|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/matches/fixtures/first-team/201819/august/nottingham-forest-vs-reading-on-11-aug-18/#|website=readingfc.co.uk|publisher=Reading F.C.|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> On 14 August Reading hosted [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] in the First Round of the [[EFL Cup]], with goals from [[Yakou M\u00e9\u00eft\u00e9]] and [[John Swift (footballer, born 1995)|John Swift]] securing Reading's first win of the season and their place in the Second Round of the League Cup.<ref name=\"MATCHREPORT Birmingham City H (EFL Cup)\" group=\"Report\">{{cite web|title=Reading 2\u20130 Birmingham City|url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/matches/fixtures/first-team/201819/august/reading-vs-birmingham-city-on-13-aug-18/#|website=readingfc.co.uk|publisher=Reading F.C.|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 August, [[Axel \u00d3skar Andr\u00e9sson|Axel Andr\u00e9sson]] signed a new contract with Reading until the summer of 2020, and then immediately joined Norwegian [[1. divisjon|OBOS-ligaen]] club [[Viking FK]] on loan until the end of their season.<ref name=\"Andresson 2020\">{{cite web |title=Andresson pens extension and agrees Viking loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/august/andresson-pens-extension-and-agrees-viking-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=15 August 2018 |date=15 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 August, goalkeeper Liam Driscoll joined [[Hungerford Town F.C.|Hungerford Town]] on an emergency loan after J\u00f6kull Andr\u00e9sson was ruled out for a couple of week due to injury in a prior game.<ref name=\"Liam Driscoll\">{{cite web |title=Liam Driscoll Hungerford Town |url=https://twitter.com/HungerfordTown/status/1030449898653712384 |website=twitter.com |publisher=Hungerford Town Twitter |accessdate=17 August 2018 |date=17 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 August, Reading announced the signing of winger [[Josh Sims (footballer)|Josh Sims]] on a season-long loan deal from [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref name=\"Josh Sims\">{{cite web |title=Josh Sims arrives on season-long loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/august/josh-sims-arrives-on-season-long-loan |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=20 August 2018 |date=20 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 August, Reading announced that [[Saeid Ezatolahi]] had joined the club on a season-long loan deal from [[FC Rostov|Rostov]],<ref name=\"Saeid Ezatolahi\">{{cite web |title=Royals sign Saeid Ezatolahi on season-long loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/august/royals-sign-saeid-ezatolahi-on-season-long-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 August 2018 |date=31 August 2018}}</ref> and that [[Liam Moore]] had signed a new five-year contract, keeping him at Reading until the summer of 2023.<ref name=\"Moore 2023\">{{cite web |title=Liam Moore makes five-year commitment to club with new Royals contract |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/august/liam-moore-makes-five-year-commitment-to-club-with-new-royals-contract |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 August 2018 |date=31 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===September===\nA 2-1 defeat to Sheffield Wednesday on 1 September means Reading suffer their  most  winless season in their 147-year history despite Liam Moore's late header in the 78th minute.\n\nOn 7 September, goalkeeper [[George Legg]] joined [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] on a one-month loan deal.<ref name=\"George Legg Loan\">{{cite news |title=Keeper Joins On Loan |url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/keeper-joins-on-loan/ |accessdate=7 September 2018 |publisher=[[Aldershot Town F.C.]] |date=7 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 September, Reading confirmed that [[Brian Tevreden (footballer, born 1981)|Brian Tevreden]] had left the club to become Chief Executive at [[K.S.V. Roeselare]], with [[Gianluca Nani]] taking over as Sporting Director.\n\n===October===\nOn 3 October, Reading announced that [[Yakou M\u00e9\u00efte]] had signed a new contract with Reading, until the summer of 2022.<ref name=\"M\u00e9\u00efte 2022\">{{cite web |title=M\u00e9\u00eft\u00e9 pens new long-term deal as a Royal |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/october/meite-pens-new-long-term-deal-as-a-royal/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=3 October 2018 |date=3 October 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 October 2018, [[Gabriel Osho]] joined [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] on loan until 4 November 2018, whilst Ade Shokunbi joined [[Billericay Town F.C.|Billericay Town]] until January 2019.<ref name=\"Osho & Shokunbi\">{{cite web |title=Shokunbi and Osho depart on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/october/shokunbi-and-osho-depart-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=5 October 2018 |date=5 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n===November===\nOn 7 November, [[Gabriel Osho]] had his loan with [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]] extended until the New Year,<ref name=\"Osho Loan Extended\">{{cite web |title=Loan update {{!}} Smith scores; Axel on top; Osho extended |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/november/loan-update--smith-scores-axel-on-top-osho-extended/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=17 November 2018 |date=7 November 2018}}</ref> with [[Josh Barrett (footballer)|Josh Barrett]] joining Osho at Aldershot Town on 10 November, signing an initial one-month loan deal<ref name=\"Barrett Loan\">{{cite news |title=Barrett loaned to Aldershot in time for Bradford match |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/november/barrett-loaned-to-aldershot-in-time-for-bradford-match/ |accessdate=10 November 2018 |publisher=[[Reading F.C.]] |date=10 November 2018}}</ref>\nOn 16 November, [[George Legg]] joined [[Braintree Town F.C.|Braintree Town]] on a month-long loan deal, whilst Adam Liddle and [[Joel Rollinson]] signed youth loan moves with [[Eastbourne Borough F.C.|Eastbourne Borough]] until 16 December.<ref name=\"Trio Loaned Out\">{{cite web |title=Trio seal loan moves and could earn minutes this weekend! |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/november/trio-seal-loan-moves-and-could-earn-minutes-this-weekend/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=17 November 2018 |date=16 November 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 19 November, [[Ron Gourlay]] left his role as [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of Reading with immediate effect.<ref>{{cite web |title=Club statement Gourlay steps down as CEO |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/november/club-statement--gourlay-steps-down-as-ceo/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=19 November 2018 |date=19 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n===December===\nOn 3 December, Reading were drawn away to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] by [[Ruud Gullit]] and [[Paul Ince]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Emirates FA Cup Third Round Draw Made At Stamford Bridge |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2018/dec/03/fa-cup-third-round-draw-031218 |publisher=[[The Football Association]] |accessdate=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Paul Clement (football manager)|Paul Clement]] was sacked as manager on 6 December,<ref>{{cite web |title=Club statement Royals part company with Paul Clement |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/december/club-statement--royals-part-company-with-paul-clement/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=7 December 2018 |date=6 December 2018}}</ref> with U23 manager [[Scott Marshall (footballer)|Scott Marshall]] taking temporary charge of the first team,<ref>{{cite web |title=Scott Marshall taking first-team training |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/december/scott-marshall-taking-first-team-training/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=7 December 2018 |date=6 December 2018}}</ref> and [[Gabriel Osho]] being recalled early from his loan deal with [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]].<ref name=\"Osho recalled\">{{cite web |title=PLAYER UPDATE |url=https://www.theshots.co.uk/player-update/ |website=theshots.co.uk |publisher=Aldershot Town F.C. |accessdate=7 December 2018 |date=6 December 2018}}</ref> The following day, 7 December, [[Gianluca Nani]] left the club by mutual consent less than three months after joining Reading.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gianluca Nani leaves his position as Sporting Director |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/december/gianluca-nani-leaves-his-position-as-sporting-director |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=7 December 2018 |date=7 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 December, young midfielder Tyler Frost joined [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] on a month-long loan deal.<ref name=\"Frost Loan\">{{cite web |title=TYLER FROST JOINS ON LOAN |url=https://www.havantandwaterloovillefc.co.uk/articles/2018/12/16/tyler-frost-joins-on-loan.html |website=havantandwaterloovillefc.co.uk |publisher=Havant & Waterlooville F.C. |accessdate=24 December 2018 |date=16 December 2018}}</ref>\nOn 20 December, Reading announced that [[Adrian Popa (footballer, born 1988)|Adrian Popa]] had moved to [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] on loan for the rest of the season,<ref name=\"Ludogorets Razgrad Loan Popa\">{{cite web |title=Popa set to spend rest of season on loan at Ludogorets |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/december/popa-set-to-spend-rest-of-season-on-loan-at-ludogorets/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=20 December 2018 |date=20 December 2018}}</ref> with [[Axel \u00d3skar Andr\u00e9sson|Axel Andr\u00e9sson]] moving to [[Viking FK]] on permanent deal the following day.<ref name=\"Andresson Leaves\">{{cite web |title=Andresson makes permanent switch to Viking |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/december/andresson-makes-permanent-switch-to-viking/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=21 December 2018 |date=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 December, [[Wealdstone F.C.|Wealdstone]] announced the signing of Ramarni Medford-Smith on loan for one-month.<ref name=\"Medford-Smith Wealdstone signed\">{{cite web |title=NEW LOAN SIGNING: |url=https://www.wealdstone-fc.com/news-blog/player-news-6 |website=wealdstone-fc.com/ |publisher=Wealdstone F.C. |accessdate=18 January 2019 |date=21 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nFollowing Readings 1-0 home defeat to [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] on 22 December, Reading announced the appointment of [[Jos\u00e9 Manuel Gomes|Jos\u00e9 Gomes]] as their new manager.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jos\u00e9 Gomes confirmed as new Royals boss |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2018/december/jose-gomes-confirmed-as-new-royals-boss2/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=22 December 2018 |date=22 December 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 December, goalkeeper [[Luke Southwood]] joined [[Eastleigh F.C.|Eastleigh]] on a one-month loan deal.\n\n===January===\n====Transfers====\nOn 29 December 2018, [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] announced that [[Sam Smith (footballer, born 1998)|Sam Smith]] would return to Reading earl from his loan deal, after they'd activated a clause in the contract.<ref name=\"Sam Smith Loan Ends\">{{cite web |title=Sam Smith leaves Oxford United with Tony McMahon on verge of exit |url=https://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/sport/oxfordunited/usnews/17325658.sam-smith-leaves-oxford-united-with-tony-mcmahon-on-verge-of-exit/ |website=oxfordmail.co.uk/ |publisher=Oxford Mail |accessdate=1 January 2019 |date=29 December 2018}}</ref>\nOn 3 January 2019, [[Pelle Clement]] left the club to join [[Eredivisie]] club [[PEC Zwolle]], who were managed by Ex-Reading manager [[Jaap Stam]].<ref name=\"Pelle Clement to PEC Zwolle\">{{cite web |title=Pelle Clement signs for PEC Zwolle |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/pelle-clement-signs-for-pec-zwolle/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=3 January 2019 |date=3 January 2019}}</ref> The following day [[Ben House]] joined [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] on loan until the end of the season,<ref name=\"Ben House Swindon\">{{cite web |title=Ben House to head to Swindon on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/ben-house-to-head-to-swindon-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=4 January 2019 |date=4 January 2019}}</ref> whilst [[Darren Sidoel]] joined [[K.S.V. Roeselare]] on loan until the end if the season.<ref name=\"Darren Sidoel loan\">{{cite web |title= Darren Sidoel seals loan switch to KSV Roeselare |url= https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/darren-sidoel-seals-loan-switch-to-ksv-roeselare/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=4 January 2019 |date=4 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 January, Reading announced that [[David Edwards (footballer)|David Edwards]] had left the club to re-join [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]],<ref name=\"Edwards to Shrewsbury\">{{cite web |title=Edwards departs to return to his Shrewsbury roots |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/edwards-departs-to-return-to-his-shrewsbury-roots/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=7 January 2019 |date=7 January 2019}}</ref> whilst [[Josh Sims (footballer)|Josh Sims]]' loan deal had been ended early and he'd returned to [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]],<ref name=\"Sims returns to Southampton\">{{cite web |title=Josh Sims returns to Southampton |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/josh-sims-returns-to-southampton/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=7 January 2019 |date=7 January 2019}}</ref> and [[Ovie Ejaria]] joined on loan until the end of the season from [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref name=\"Ejaria Loan\">{{cite web |title=Ovie Ejaria completes loan move to the Madejski |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/ovie-ejaria-completes-loan-move-to-the-madejski/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=7 January 2019 |date=7 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 January, [[Lewis Baker (footballer)|Lewis Baker]] joined Reading on loan for the remainder of the season from [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]].<ref name=\"Baker Loan\">{{cite web |title=Royals land Lewis Baker on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/royals-land-lewis-baker-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=9 January 2019 |date=9 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 January, Reading announced that [[Lewis Ward (footballer)|Lewis Ward]]'s loan with [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] had ended early, and that he would join [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref name=\"Ward Joins Forest Green Rovers\">{{cite web |title=Ward Starts Fresh New Loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/ward-starts-fresh-new-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=14 January 2019 |date=14 January 2019}}</ref>\nOn 18 January, Reading announced that [[George Legg]] had joined [[Boreham Wood F.C.|Boreham Wood]] on loan until the end of the season,<ref name=\"Legg Boreham Wood\">{{cite web |title=WOOD HAVE A STRONG LEGG TO STAND ON |url=https://www.borehamwoodfootballclub.co.uk/uncategorized/wood-have-a-strong-legg-to-stand-on/ |website=borehamwoodfootballclub.co.uk |publisher=Boreham Wood F.C. |accessdate=18 January 2019 |date=18 January 2019}}</ref> [[Sam Smith (footballer, born 1998)|Sam Smith]] had joined [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] until the end of the season,<ref name=\"Sam Smith Shrewsbury Town\">{{cite web |title=Sam Smith begins loan spell as a Shrew |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/sam-smith-begins-loan-spell-as-a-shrew |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=18 January 2019 |date=18 January 2019}}</ref> and Tyler Frost and Ramarni Medford-Smith had extended their loans with [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]] and [[Wealdstone F.C.|Wealdstone]] respectively for an additional month.<ref name=\"Medford-Smith Wealdstone twitter\">{{cite web |title=TEAM NEWS |url=https://twitter.com/wealdstonefc/status/1086271296252473345 |website=twitter.com |publisher=Wealdstone F.C. Twitter |accessdate=18 January 2019 |date=18 January 2019}}</ref>\nOn 22 January, Reading announced the singing of [[N\u00e9lson Oliveira]] on loan from [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] until the end of the season.<ref name=\"N\u00e9lson Oliveira Loan\">{{cite web |title=N\u00e9lson Oliveira joins the Royals on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/nelson-oliveira-joins-the-royals-on-loan |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=22 January 2019 |date=22 January 2019}}</ref> The next day, 23 January, [[Emiliano Mart\u00ednez]] joined on loan from [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] for the remainder of the season.<ref name=\"Emiliano Mart\u00ednez Loan\">{{cite web |title=Emiliano Mart\u00ednez signs loan move to the Madejski |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/emiliano-martinez-signs-loan-move-to-the-madejski/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=23 January 2019 |date=23 January 2019}}</ref>\nOn 24 January, [[Luke Southwood]] extended his loan deal with [[Eastleigh F.C.|Eastleigh]] until the end of the season.<ref name=\"Southwood Loan Extended\">{{cite web |title=Eastleigh Football Club is delighted to announce that Luke Southwood has had his loan extended until the end of the season. |url=https://twitter.com/EastleighFC/status/1088480085261336576 |website=twitter.com/EastleighFC/ |publisher=Eastleigh F.C. |accessdate=24 January 2019 |date=24 January 2019}}</ref> The following day [[Matt Miazga]] became the second [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]   players to join Reading on loan for the rest of the season.<ref name=\"Matt Miazga Loan\">{{cite web |title=Matt Miazga makes Madejski move on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/matt-miazga-makes-madejski-move-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=25 January 2019 |date=25 January 2019}}</ref>\nOn 29 January, [[Gabriel Osho]] joined [[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]] on loan for the remainder of the season,<ref name=\"Osho joins Bristol Rovers on loan\">{{cite web |title=Osho joins Bristol Rovers on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/osho-joins-bristol-rovers-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=29 January 2019 |date=29 January 2019}}</ref> whilst [[Tiago Ilori]] moved permanently to [[Sporting CP]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref name=\"Ilori to Sporting CP\">{{cite web |title=Ilori departs to sign for Sporting Lisbon |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/ilori-departs-to-sign-for-sporting-lisbon/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=29 January 2019 |date=29 January 2019}}</ref> On 31 January, transfer deadline day, [[Leandro Bacuna]] left the club for [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] on an undisclosed fee,<ref name=\"Leandro Bacuna Leaves\">{{cite web |title=Bacuna becomes a Bluebird on deadline day |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/bacuna-becomes-a-bluebird-on-deadline-day/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 January 2019 |date=31 January 2019}}</ref> and [[David Meyler]] and [[Marc McNulty]] left the club on loan for the remainder of the season, joining [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] and [[Hibernian F.C.|Hibernian]] respectively.<ref name=\"David Meyler Loan\">{{cite web |title=Meyler signs as a Sky Blue on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/meyler-signs-as-a-sky-blue-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 January 2019 |date=31 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Marc McNulty Loan\">{{cite web |title=McNulty signs for Hibernian on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/january/mcnulty-signs-for-hibernian-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=31 January 2019 |date=31 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===February===\nOn 6 February, [[Salisbury F.C.|Salisbury]] announced that Liam Driscoll had joined them on loan, replacing follow Reading youth keeper James Hillson who'd moved to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on loan.<ref name=\"Driscoll & Hillson Loans\">{{cite web |title=More player news |url=https://www.salisburyfc.co.uk/index.php/news/1408-more-player-news |website=salisburyfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Salisbury F.C> |accessdate=7 February 2019 |date=6 February 2019}}</ref>\nOn 10 February, [[Vito Mannone]] joined [[Minnesota United FC|Minnesota United]] on loan terms which run until 1 January 2020.<ref name=\"Mannone Loan\">{{cite web |title=Mannone makes MLS move to join Minnesota United on loan |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/february/mannone-makes-mls-move-to-join-minnesota-united-on-loan/ |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=11 February 2019 |date=10 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 February, [[Andy Rinomhota]] signed a new contract with Reading, lasting until the summer of 2022.<ref name=\"Andy Rinomhota 2022\">{{cite web |title=Rinomhota extends Reading deal until 2022 |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/february/rinomhota-extends-reading-deal-until-2022/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=25 February 2019 |date=25 February 2019}}</ref> The following day, [[Tom McIntyre]], [[Teddy Howe]] and Jordan Holsgrove extended their contracts until the summer of 2021,<ref name=\"Four New Contracts\"/> [[Tom Holmes (footballer)|Tom Holmes]] signed a new contract until the summer of 2022,<ref name=\"Four New Contracts\">{{cite web |title=Holmes, Holsgrove, Howe and McIntyre sign new professional contracts |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/february/holmes-holsgrove-howe-and-mcintyre-sign-new-professional-contracts/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=26 February 2019 |date=26 February 2019}}</ref> and [[Sone Aluko]] moved to [[Beijing Renhe F.C.|Beijing Renhe]] on loan until the end of the [[2019 Beijing Renhe F.C. season|2019 season]].<ref name=\"Aluko Loan\">{{cite web |title=Aluko completes loan move to Beijing Renhe |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/february/aluko-completes-loan-move-to-beijing-renhe/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=26 February 2019 |date=26 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===March===\nOn 12 March, [[Ryan East]] signed a new contract, until the summer of 2021, and made his first team debut against [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref name=\"East 2021\">{{cite web |title=East pens new contract on brink of first team bow |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/march/east-pens-new-contract-on-brink-of-first-team-bow/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=13 March 2019 |date=12 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===April===\nOn 17 April, Reading announced that [[Macron (sportswear)|Macron]] would be the teams new kit supplier for three-seasons beginning at the start of the 2019-20 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Royals announce new partnership with Macron |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/april/royals-announce-new-partnership-with-macron/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=17 April 2019 |date=17 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n===May===\nOn 10 May Reading announced that they had offered new contracts to Tyler Frost, Adam Liddle, Ramarni Medford-Smith, Adam Desbois, Marcel Elva-Fountaine and Roberto Nditi and a first professional deal to Imari Samuels. Reading also confirmed that first team members [[George Legg]], [[Anssi Jaakkola]], [[Paul McShane (footballer)|Paul McShane]], [[Danzell Gravenberch]], [[Callum Harriott]] and [[Joey van den Berg]] would all leave the club following the completion of their contracts at the end of June, with [[John O'Shea]] retiring from football. Also leaving the club would be youngsters Jamal Balogun, Cameron Green, Moroyin Omolabi, [[Joel Rollinson]], Ademola Shokunbi, Jazz Wallace, Jacob Pemberton, James Hillson. Shamar Moore, Terrance Saydee, Khalid Simmo and Thomas Stevens.<ref name=\"Released Retained\">{{cite web |title=New deals offered to Academy talents as first team contracts expire |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/may/new-deals-offered-to-academy-talents-as-first-team-contracts-expire |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=10 May 2019 |date=10 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 May 2019, [[Michael Olise]] was called up to the [[France national under-18 football team|France]] at the [[2019 Toulon Tournament]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Lo\u00efc Mbe Soh and Arthur Zagre with France U18 |url=https://www.psg.fr/equipes/the-club/content/loiec-mbe-soh-et-arthur-zagre-avec-la-france-u18-1 |website=psg.fr/ |publisher=Paris Saint-Germain F.C. |accessdate=27 May 2019 |language=French |date=27 May 2019}}</ref> whilst the following day [[Danny Loader]] was called up to represent [[England national under-20 football team|England]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Loader gets Three Lions call for Toulon Tournament |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/may/loader-gets-three-lions-call-for-toulon-tournament/ |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=28 May 2019 |date=28 May 2019}}</ref> and [[Josh Barrett (footballer)|Josh Barrett]] to represent [[Republic of Ireland national under-21 football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ireland U21: Farrugia ruled out of Toulon Tournament |url=https://www.fai.ie/ireland/news/ireland-u21-farrugia-ruled-out-of-toulon-tournament |website=fai.ie/ |publisher=Football Association of Ireland |accessdate=28 May 2019 |date=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 May, youth team goalkeeper Coniah Boyce-Clarke agreed to sign a professional contract which Reading, until the summer of 2023, to commence the summer after his 17th birthday. On the same day, Claudio Gomes Osorio, Nelson Abbey and Malachi Talent-Aryeetey agreed to sign professional terms with the club once they turn 17.<ref name=\"Boyce-Clarke 2023\">{{cite web |title=Boyce-Clarke commits to long-term Royals contract |url=https://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/2019/may/boyce-clarke-commits-to-long-term-royals-contract |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=28 May 2019 |date=28 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Transfers==\n{{Main|List of English football transfers summer 2018|List of English football transfers winter 2018\u201319}}\n\n===In===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; \"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#00f; color:white; width:140px;\"| Date\n! style=\"background:#00f; color:white; width:50px;\"| Position\n! styl